OL,7,FThe cups can break down into
OL,8,Fmicroplastics which threaten wildlife
OL,9,Fand water quality.
OL,11,F"The Thames is the lifeblood of London
OL,12,Fand it's really important that we
OL,13,Fimprove the quality of the river for
OL,14,Fboth humans and all the animals living
OL,15,Fwithin it," said Emily.
OL,17,F"The water quality is really
OL,18,Fimportant. The Thames has come a long
OL,19,Fway. It was declared biologically dead
OL,20,Fin the 50s and now we've got 125
OL,21,Fspecies of fish living in the river.
